    NOTE["Different clients → different atomics → fully parallel, zero interference.<br/>Same client → one AtomicReference → CAS serializes the check-and-consume,<br/>so the limit holds EXACTLY (no lost-update race lets extra requests through).<br/>Lock-free hot path; bounded memory via idle-client eviction.<br/>Alternative: a per-bucket ReentrantLock (correct too, but CAS avoids blocking)."]:::note

